Test Header Number / Size of Hose
children.hint: Test Header Number / Size of Hose

children.title: Roof Manifold Number / Size of Hose
children.hint: Roof Manifold Number / Size of Hose

children.title: Pump suction, discharge and by-pass control valves fully open, and piping free of leaks (8.2.2(2))
children.hint: 8.2.2(2(a)) Pump suction and discharge and bypass valves are fully open. (b) Piping is free of leaks.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Wet pit suction screens unobstructed and in place. (8.2.2(2))
children.hint: (8.2.2(2f)) Wet pit suction screens are unobstructed and in place.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Pressure (psi) shown on Suction side pressure gauge. ((8.2.2(2))
children.hint: 8.2.2 (2(c)) Suction line pressure gauge reading is within acceptable range.

children.title: Pressure (psi) shown on System side pressure gauge. ((8.2.2(2))
children.hint: 8.2.2(2(d)) System line pressure gauge reading is within acceptable range.

children.title: Waterflow valve in closed position, hose connection valve is closed & line to test valve free of water. (8.2.2(2))
children.hint: 8.2.2(2(g)) Waterflow test valves are in the closed position, the hose connection valve is closed, and the line to test valves is free of water.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Suction reservoir has required level. (8.2.2(2))
children.hint: (8.2.2(2e)) Suction reservoir has the required water level.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Fuel tank at least two-thirds full. (8.2.2(4))
children.hint: (8.2.2(4a)) Fuel tank is at least two-thirds full.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Controller selector switch in AUTO position. (8.2.2(4))
children.hint: (8.2.2(4b)) Controller selector switch is in auto position.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Batteries voltage and charging current readings within normal range. (8.2.2(4))
children.hint: (8.2.2(4c)) Batteries’ (2) voltage readings are within acceptable range. (8.2.2(4d)) Batteries’ (2) charging current readings are within acceptable range.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Batteries pilot lights ON or batteries failure pilot lights OFF. (8.2.2(4))
children.hint: (8.2.2(4e)) Batteries’ (2) pilot lights are on or battery failure (2) pilot lights are off.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Electrolyte level in batteries normal and terminals free from corrosion. (8.2.2(4))
children.hint: 8.2.2(4)(k) Electrolyte level in batteries is within acceptable range. (l) Battery terminals are free from corrosion.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
All alarm pilot lights OFF. (8.2.2(4))
children.hint: 8.2.2(4)(f) All alarm pilot lights are off.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Crankcase oil, right angle gear level and cooling water level in acceptable range and water-jacket heater operating. (8.2.2(4))
children.hint: 8.2.2(4)(h) Oil level in right angle gear drive is within acceptable range. (i) Crankcase oil level is within acceptable range. (j) Cooling water level is within acceptable range. (m) Water-jacket heater is operating.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Engine running time from meter reading (mins.). (8.2.2(4))
children.hint: 8.2.2(4(g)) Engine running time meter is reading.

children.title: Time (sec.) for engine to crank. (8.3.2.9(3))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(3a)) Observe the time for engine to crank.

children.title: Time (sec.) for engine to reach running speed. (8.3.2.9(3))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(3b)) Observe the time for engine to reach running speed.

children.title: Record pump starting pressure. (8.3.2.9(1(a))
children.hint: 8.3.2.9(1a)) Record the pump starting pressure from the pressure switch or pressure transducer.

children.title: Check for slight discharge from packing glands; Pump free from any unusual noise or vibration. (8.3.2.9(1))
children.hint: 8.3.2.9(1c)) Inspect the pump packing glands for slight discharge. (d) Adjust gland nuts if necessary. (e) Inspect for unusual noise or vibration.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Packing boxes, bearing, or pump casing maintain an acceptable temperature during the test. (8.3.2.9(1))
children.hint: 8.3.2.9(1(f))  Inspect packing boxes, bearings, or pump casing for overheating.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Engine oil pressure, speed indicator, water and oil temperature indicator readings normal during test. (8.3.2.9(3))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(3c)) Observe the engine oil pressure gauge, speed indicator, water, and oil temperature indicators periodically while engine is running.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Cooling water flowing from the heat exchanger during test. (8.3.2.9(3))
children.hint: 8.3.2.9(3)(e) Inspect the heat exchanger for cooling waterflow.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Exhaust system, drain condensate traps & silencers in good working condition. (8.1.1.2.13)
children.hint: 8.1.1.2.13 Exhaust systems, drain condensate traps, and silencers shall be checked annually.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Pump operated and tested for 30 minutes. ( 8.3.2.4)
children.hint: 8.3.2.4 The diesel pump shall run a minimum of 30 minutes.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Fire pump alarm conditions and supervisory sensors operate when tested through simulation. (8.3.3.10)
children.hint: 8.3.3.10 Alarm conditions shall be simulated by activating alarm circuits at alarm sensor locations, and all such local or remote alarm indicating devices (visual and audible) shall be observed for operation.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Parallel and angular alignment of pump and driver without any misalignments. (8.3.6.4)
children.hint: (8.3.6.4) Parallel and angular alignement of the pump and driver shall be inspected during the annual test, and any misalignment shall be corrected.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Suction screens inspected and cleaned after waterflow. (8.3.3.12)
children.hint: 8.3.3.12 Suction Screens. After the waterflow portions of the annual test or fire protection system activations, the suction screens shall be inspected and cleared of any debris or obstructions.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Pressure gauges and sensors, when compared to a calibrated gauge, less than 5% out of calibration, or gauge or sensor has been recalibrated or replaced. (Table 8.1.2))
children.hint: Table 8.1.2  The accuracy of pressure gauges and sensors shall be inspected annually and replaced or recalibrated when more than 5 percent out of calibration

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
OVERALL CONDITION
children.hint: 8.3.7.2.3 The fire pump test results shall be considered acceptable if both of the following conditions are satisfied: (1) Fire pump can supply the full system demand as provided by the owner. (2) Fire pump test results are no less than 95 percent of the flow rates and pressures at each point for either a or b: (a) Original unadjusted field test curve (b) Fire pump nameplate

children.title: Pump suction, discharge and by-pass control valves fully open,and piping free of leaks. (8.2.2(2))
children.hint: 8.2.2(2(a)) Pump suction and discharge and bypass valves are fully open. (b) Piping is free of leaks.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Suction line pressure gauge reading is within acceptable range. (8.2.2(2c))
children.hint: 8.2.2 (2(c)) Suction line pressure gauge reading is within acceptable range. 8.3.2.1.2.1 The pressure readings on the discharge and suction gauges shall be recorded, and a pressure difference that is greater than 95 percent of the rated pump pressure shall be investigated and corrected.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
System line pressure gauge reading is within acceptable range. (8.2.2(2d))
children.hint: 8.2.2(2(d)) System line pressure gauge reading is within acceptable range. 8.3.2.1.2.1 The pressure readings on the discharge and suction gauges shall be recorded, and a pressure difference that is greater than 95 percent of the rated pump pressure shall be investigated and corrected.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Suction reservoir has required water level & wet pit suction screen in place and unobstructed. (8.2.2(2))
children.hint: 8.2.2 (2) Pump system conditions are determined as follows: (e) Suction reservoir has the required water level. (f) Wet pit suction screens are unobstructed and in place.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Waterflow valve in closed position, hose connection valve closed, test valve line free of water. (8.2.2(2))
children.hint: (8.2.2(2g)) Waterflow test valves are in the closed position, the hose connection valve is closed, and the line to test valves is free of water.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Controller pilot light (power on) illuminated (8.2.2(3))
children.hint: (8.2.2(3)) Electrical system conditions are determined as follows: (a) Controller pilot light (power on) is illuminated. (d) Reverse phase alarm pilot light is off, or normal phase rotation pilot light is on.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Oil level in vertical motor sight glass, if available, within acceptable range. (8.2.2(3))
children.hint: (8.2.2(3)) Electrical system conditions are determined as follows: (e) Oil level in vertical motor sight glass is within acceptable range.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Power to Jockey pump is provided, if applicable. (8.2.2(3))
children.hint: (8.2.2(3)) Electrical system conditions are determined as follows: (f) Power to pressure maintenance (jockey) pump is provided.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Jockey pump sensing line gauge start pressure
Jockey pump sensing line gauge stop pressure
Jockey pump gauge when compared to calibrated gauge, is less than 5% out of calibration or gauge has been recalibrated or replaced.  (Table 8.1.2)
Take a picture of the issue
Record pump starting pressure. (8.3.2.9(1a))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(1a)) Record the pump starting pressure from the pressure switch or pressure transducer.

children.title: Record the system suction pressure gauge readings with pump running. (8.3.2.9(1b))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(1b)) Record the system suction pressure gauge readings.

children.title: Time (sec) controller is on first step. (8.3.2.9(2))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(2b)) Record the time controller is on first step (for reduced voltage or reduced current starting).

children.title: Time (sec.) for driver to accelerate to full speed. (8.3.2.9(2))
children.hint: 8.3.2.9(2a) Observe the time for motor to accelerate to full speed.

children.title: Record time pump runs after starting (for auto stop controller). (8.3.2.9(2))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(2c)) Record the time pump runs after starting (for automatic stop controllers).

children.title: Record the discharge pressure gauge readings with pump running. (8.3.2.9(1b))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(1b)) Record the discharge pressure gauge readings.

children.title: With pump running, check for slight discharge from packing glands; Pump free from any unusual noise or vibration. (8.3.2.9(1))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(1c)) Inspect the pump packing glands for slight discharge. (8.3.2.9(1e)) Inspect for unusual noise or vibration.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Packing boxes, bearing, or pump casing maintain an acceptable temperature during the test. (8.3.2.9(1))
children.hint: (8.3.2.9(1f)) Inspect packing boxes, bearings, or pump casing for overheating.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Pump run minimum 10 minutes. (8.3.2.3)
children.hint: (8.3.2.3) The electric pump shall run a minimum of 10 minutes.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Fire pump alarm conditions and supervisory sensors operate when tested through simulation. (8.3.3.10)
children.hint: (8.3.3.10) Alarm conditions shall be simulated by activating alarm circuits at alarm sensor locations, and all such local or remote alarm indicating devices (visual and audible) shall be observed for operation.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Parallel and angular alignment of pump and driver without any misalignments. (8.3.6.4)
children.hint: (8.3.6.4) Parallel and angular alignement of the pump and driver shall be inspected during the annual test, and any misalignment shall be corrected.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Suction screens inspected and cleaned after water flow. (8.3.3.12)
children.hint: (8.3.3.12) Suction Screens. After the waterflow portions of the annual test or fire protection system activations, the suction screens shall be inspected and cleared of any debris or obstructions.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Pressure gauge and sensors, when compared to a calibrated gauge, is less than 5% calibration or have been recalibrated or replaced. (Table 8.1.2 )
children.hint: (Table 8.1.2 )  The accuracy of pressure gauges and sensors shall be inspected annually and replaced or recalibrated when more than 5 percent out of calibration

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
OVERALL CONDITION
children.hint: 8.3.7.2.3 The fire pump test results shall be considered acceptable if both of the following conditions are satisfied: (1) Fire pump can supply the full system demand as provided by the owner. (2) Fire pump test results are no less than 95 percent of the flow rates and pressures at each point for either a or b: (a) Original unadjusted field test curve (b) Fire pump nameplate

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Pressure downstream of the relief valve fittings in discharge piping does not exceed pressure system rating.  (13.5.7.2.2)
children.hint: 13.5.7.2.2 The inspection shall verify that the pressure downstream of the relief valve fittings in the fire pump discharge piping does not exceed the pressure for which the system components are rated.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Valve, under test conditions, relieves at correct pressure and closes below that pressure.  (13.5.7.2.3)
children.hint: 13.5.7.2.3 During the annual fire pump flow test, the pressure relief valve shall be verified to be correctly adjusted and set to relieve at the correct pressure and to close below that pressure setting.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Verify water flows through valve when fire pump is operating at shutoff pressure. (13.5.7.1.2)
children.hint: 13.5.7.1.2 The inspection shall verify that water flows through the valve when the fire pump is operating at shutoff pressure (i.e., churn) to prevent the pump from overheating.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Valve not leaking, in open position and handwheel unbroken.   (13.5.1.1)
children.hint: 13.5.1.1 All valves shall be inspected quarterly to verify that the valves are in the following condition: (1) In the open position  (2) Not leaking

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Verify closure of valve at end of test.  (13.5.7.1.3)
children.hint: 13.5.7.1.3 On completion of any fire pump test, the closure of the circulation relief valve shall be verified.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Valve has proper signs, and is accessible.  (13.3.2.2)
children.hint: 13.3.2.2  The valve inspection shall verify that the valves are in the following condition: (3) Accessible  (6) Provided with applicable identification

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Valve is free of external leaks, and appropriate wrench available for PIV.   (13.3.2.2)
children.hint: 13.3.2.2  The valve inspection shall verify that the valves are in the following condition: (4) Post indicator valves (PIVs) are provided with correct wrenches  (5) Free from external leaks

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Valve in normal  position and properly secured.  (13.3.2.2)
children.hint: 13.3.2.2  The valve inspection shall verify that the valves are in the following condition: (1) In the normal open or closed position (2) Sealed, locked, or supervised

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Valve exercised through full range to ensure proper operation.  (13.3.3.1)
children.hint: 13.3.3.1 Each control valve shall be operated annually through its full range and returned to its normal position.  13.3.3.2 Post indicator valves shall be opened until spring or torsion is felt in the rod, indicating that the rod has not become detached from the valve.  13.3.3.3 Post indicator and outside screw and yoke valves shall be backed a one-quarter turn from the fully open position to prevent jamming.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Valve Status Test - Valves open when returned to service.  (13.3.1.2.1)
children.hint: 13.3.1.2.1  When the valve is returned to service, a valve status test (either main or sectional drain, as appropriate) shall be conducted to determine that the valve is not closed.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Visual inspection verifies unit was free of physical damage.
children.hint: 13.3.2.1.2  Control valve supervisory alarm devices shall be inspected quarterly to verify that they are free of physical damage.

children.title: Take a picture of the issue
Operational test results in distinctive signal when valve position moves out of normal.
children.hint: 13.3.3.5.1 Valve supervisory switches shall be tested semiannually. 13.3.3.5.2  A distinctive signal shall indicate movement from the valve’s normal position during either the first two revolutions of a hand wheel or when the stem of the valve has moved one-fifth of the distance from its normal position.

Liability Release Statement
children.calculate_expr: "The owner and/or designated representative acknowledges the responsibility of the operating condition of the component parts at the time of this inspection. It is agreed that the inspection service provided by the contractor as prescribed herein is limited to performing a visual inspection and/or routine testing, and any investigation or unscheduled testing, modification, maintenance, repair, etc., of the component parts is not included as part of the inspection work performed. It is further understood that all information contained herein is provided to the best of the knowledge of the party providing such information."
